query:
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content)
SELECT id, 'N-002', 'Seizure Protocol', 'Neurological',
'SEIZURE PROTOCOL

ASSESSMENT: Protect patient from injury. Note seizure characteristics and duration. Check blood glucose. Look for medical alert jewelry.

ACTIVE SEIZURE MANAGEMENT:
1. AIRWAY/BREATHING - Position on side when safe. Suction as needed. Do NOT force anything in mouth. Oxygen via NRB.

2. BLOOD GLUCOSE - Check immediately. Treat hypoglycemia if <60 mg/dL.

3. BENZODIAZEPINES (Status Epilepticus >5 minutes)
MIDAZOLAM (Preferred): IM 10mg (adult), 0.2mg/kg (peds, max 10mg). IN 0.2mg/kg per nostril (max 10mg total). IV/IO 0.1mg/kg (max 4mg).
LORAZEPAM: IV 4mg (adult), 0.1mg/kg (peds, max 4mg). May repeat once in 5 minutes.
DIAZEPAM: IV 5-10mg (adult), 0.1mg/kg (peds, max 4mg). PR 0.2mg/kg (max 10mg) for peds.

4. IF SEIZURES CONTINUE - Repeat benzodiazepine x1. Prepare for airway management. Rapid transport.

POST-ICTAL CARE: Recovery position. Reassess airway frequently. Monitor for recurrence. Assess for injuries.

SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS: Eclampsia: Magnesium 4-6g IV. Febrile seizure (peds): Usually self-limited. Known epileptic: May have rescue meds.'
FROM counties;
